A car bomb exploded in the central part of Erbil, injuring one person severely, local media sources reported on Monday. Local media sources reported on Monday that the sound of an explosion was heard in Erbil, the capital of Iraq’s Kurdistan region. According to the local media, the explosion was caused by the detonation of a car bomb in a neighborhood in central Erbil. -Advertisement- Preliminary reports suggest that an individual has been critically wounded in the explosion. No details have been released about the incident.